    "body": "<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`: v0.4.4\r\n- `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: ) behaves differently? No\r\n- Operating system/version: Arch Linux (rolling release)\r\n- Terminal name/version: `rxvt-unicode (urxvt) v9.22`\r\n- `$TERM`: rxvt-unicode-256color\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\ncopy and paste the following yaml into a file (sample.yml)\r\n```yaml\r\nsome_key: |\r\n  not_a_key: abc\r\n  [brackets]\r\n\r\nthis_is_a_key: def\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nnvim -u NORC sample.yml\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\nthe multiline string is treated like regular yaml lines, the result is that we get keys and other yaml syntaxes highlighted inside a multiline string\r\n![screenshot(254)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6627147/97732388-d8448b80-1aac-11eb-8531-3c59b4444a8f.png)\r\n\r\nthis is better illustrated with a vibrant colorscheme, so here is the same file but using my regular vim config\r\n![screenshot(253)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6627147/97732397-daa6e580-1aac-11eb-923d-680c5ebb88b5.png)\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\nthe content for the key `some_key` should all be highlighted as a string, which you can see in the way github highlights the yaml above ^",
    "closed_at": "2020-11-14T05:52:17Z",
